Section 1:
1 L.D. 1079
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 701, L.D. 1079, “An Act to Provide
10 Comprehensive Perimenopause and Menopause Education”
11 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
12 following:
13 'Sec. 1. 22 MRSA c. 279 is enacted to read:
14 CHAPTER 279
15 PERIMENOPAUSE AND MENOPAUSE EDUCATION
16 §1700-F. Perimenopause and menopause education materials
17 The department shall enter into partnerships with health care providers, including
18 obstetricians, gynecologists, primary care providers, nurse practitioners and physician
19 assistants, and community-based health care programs and hospitals to create and
20 disseminate informational materials in electronic and physical form to educate
21 menstruating persons and all individuals on the symptoms and processes of and other issues
22 surrounding perimenopause and menopause. The informational materials must include
23 symptoms of and treatments for perimenopause and menopause, symptoms of
24 perimenopause and menopause for which a person should contact a health care provider,
25 the biological process behind perimenopause and menopause, how to talk to family and
26 friends about perimenopause and menopause and any other information the department
27 determines necessary to prepare and educate individuals regarding perimenopause and
28 menopause.
29 Sec. 2. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
30 allocations are made.
31 HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES, DEPARTMENT OF
32 Maine Center for Disease Control and Prevention 0143
Page 1 - 132LR1262(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 701, L.D. 1079
1 Initiative: Provides funding to create and disseminate informational materials on issues
2 surrounding perimenopause and menopause.
3 GENERAL FUND 2025-26 2026-27
4 All Other $20,000 $20,000
5 __________ __________
6 GENERAL FUND TOTAL $20,000 $20,000
73 '
8 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
9 number to read consecutively.
10 SUMMARY
1111 This amendment broadens the scope of the creation of perimenopause and menopause
1122 educational materials in the bill. It adds primary care providers, nurse practitioners and
1133 physician assistants to the list of medical professionals that are specified to be included in
1144 the partnerships with the Department of Health and Human Services. It requires that all
1155 individuals be the target of educational materials rather than only menstruating persons. It
1166 requires the materials to be disseminated as well as created. The amendment changes the
1177 allocation of the chapter from the Part of the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 22 concerning
1188 hospitals and medical care into the Part concerning public health. The amendment also
1199 adds an appropriations and allocations section.
2200 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
2211 (See attached)
